# React Component Patterns

## Component Types

### Presentational Components
Pure components that receive props and render UI.

```jsx
export const ServiceCard = ({ icon, title, description }) => {
  return (
    <div className="service-card">
      <div className="service-icon">{icon}</div>
      <h3>{title}</h3>
      <p>{description}</p>
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Container Components
Components with state and business logic.

```jsx
export const ServiceList = () => {
  const [services, setServices] = useState([])
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true)
  
  useEffect(() => {
    fetchServices().then(setServices).finally(() => setLoading(false))
  }, [])
  
  if (loading) return <Loader />
  
  return (
    <div className="services-grid">
      {services.map(service => (
        <ServiceCard key={service.id} {...service} />
      ))}
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Custom Hooks Pattern

Extract reusable logic into custom hooks:

```jsx
// useLanguage.js
export const useLanguage = () => {
  const [lang, setLang] = useState(() => 
    localStorage.getItem('trendLang') || 'en'
  )
  
  const changeLanguage = (newLang) => {
    setLang(newLang)
    localStorage.setItem('trendLang', newLang)
  }
  
  return { lang, changeLanguage }
}

// Usage in component
const { lang, changeLanguage } = useLanguage()
```

## Props Patterns

### Optional Props with Defaults
```jsx
export const Button = ({ 
  variant = 'primary', 
  size = 'medium',
  children,
  onClick 
}) => {
  return (
    <button 
      className={`btn btn-${variant} btn-${size}`}
      onClick={onClick}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  )
}
```

### Children Prop
```jsx
export const Section = ({ children, id, className }) => {
  return (
    <section id={id} className={className}>
      <div className="container">
        {children}
      </div>
    </section>
  )
}
```

## Conditional Rendering

```jsx
// ✅ GOOD - Early returns
if (loading) return <Loader />
if (error) return <Error message={error} />
if (!data) return null

// ✅ GOOD - Ternary for simple conditions
{isOpen ? <Modal /> : null}

// ✅ GOOD - Logical AND for single condition
{hasServices && <ServiceList services={services} />}
```

## List Rendering

Always use stable keys:

```jsx
// ✅ GOOD - Unique ID as key
{services.map(service => (
  <ServiceCard key={service.id} {...service} />
))}

// ❌ BAD - Index as key (unstable)
{services.map((service, index) => (
  <ServiceCard key={index} {...service} />
))}
```

## Event Handlers

```jsx
<button onClick={() => setOpen(!open)}>Toggle</button>

const handleSubmit = (e) => {
  e.preventDefault()
  validateAndSubmitForm(formData)
}

<form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
```
